      "content": "The 2011 US-led intervention in Libya was a catastrophic geopolitical failure that directly led to the rise of ISIS and the collapse of the Libyan state. While the initial goal was to protect civilians under UN Resolution 1973, the US and its allies abandoned the no-fly zone mandate, allowing the National Liberation Army to seize control of the country and eventually assassinate Muammar Gaddafi. This unchecked escalation created a power vacuum that destabilized the entire Mediterranean region for decades. Geopolitically, the intervention backfired by exporting chaos rather than establishing a stable democracy, proving that military force without a clear exit strategy is dangerous.",
