    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a pretty strong take. I've seen some people argue the opposite though—like that it was a necessary response to prevent a massacre in Benghazi and that the instability was more about local tribal politics than the intervention itself. Why do you see it as such a clear failure compared to those points?",
