      "content": "The intervention was a clear failure because the US abandoned its own stated goals of protecting civilians once the fighting intensified, effectively allowing the National Liberation Army to seize power. While the Benghazi massacre was tragic, the subsequent power vacuum and tribal fragmentation were direct consequences of the US failing to secure a stable outcome, not merely local politics. Geopolitically, this decision directly facilitated the rise of extremist groups like ISIS across the region, proving that the intervention exported chaos rather than preventing it.",
